external_knowledge:
- 'catching more eyeballs' refers to receiving a higher number of views;
- 'recent' in this context means articles added after August 1, 2023;
- 'popularity' here is measured by the average number of views for articles from each category and source.

sql:
SELECT a.title, s.source_name, a.publication_date
FROM articles a
JOIN sources s ON a.source_id = s.source_id;

SELECT title
FROM articles
WHERE author = 'editor@webtribeinc.com';
